Description:
The National Army Museum (NAM) wishes to appoint a suitably qualified and experienced digital learning specialist to help us develop a new market for learning nationally, by creating a suite of materials to support Citizenship Learning in classrooms away from the Museum.

The Museum wishes to:

•	Engage KS2-3 audiences;
•	Showcase our unique collections and subject matter, and make them relevant to students today;
•	Increase digital engagement via the NAM website and other digital channels  (eg TES, show.me);
•	Develop a national footprint for our learning service;
•	Attract new ‘non-history’ audiences, and encourage a different perception of NAM, as distinct from ‘recruiting’ for the British Army.

